( Yes, I know I'm late.)

* Iron Raptor sighed and lifted her her hands into the air, she caught Prowl's talons easily.
It was a shame that her friend had chosen a path as such but it was Plintissa's life, not her own.
But now she was an enemy, and it was her own job to try and eliminate the enemies of the Maximals.
She was touched that Plintissa had taken that shot from Gangon for her but she couldn't say the same if Plintissa had been attacked.
Iron Raptor tightened her grip on Prowl's talons, at least she had other friends left, she looked up at him but then back down.
But business was at hand and there was no time to dwell on things, with the commander on some date with his girlfriend and his second-in-command at the scene already.
Iron Raptor opened her communicator to Tigerhawk.*

" Could you please give me a report on the situation, Tigerhawk? It would really be helpful so Prowl and myself would know what to expect when we get there."
